<br>
With the new UI, you can customize your skins through the editing of the XML files in your Everquest\uifiles\default directory.<br>
<br>
Now, many people are intimidated by XML. Which is why I'm starting this thread, so as to help those who want to customize but don't have the technical know-how, and also for those savy in XML and object oriented programming to share ideas and cool stuff.  <br>
<br>
Go nuts  <br>
<br>
<br>
To load a skin:<br>
<br>
- Go to your Everquest\uifiles directory.<br>
- Create a new directory. Name it whatever you wish.<br>
- Copy all the files from the Everquest\uifiles\default directory into your new one<br>
- Edit whatever files you want to in your new directory<br>
- Log into the game<br>
- Use the /loadskin &lt;your new folder name&gt; <br>
<br>
<br>
To copy your window settings from character to character:<br>
<br>
- Log into the game, and position your windows how you want them. Log out.<br>
- Go into your default Everquest directory, and locate your ini files. There will be a new one named UI_&lt;character name&gt;_82.ini.<br>
- Copy that UI.ini file, and rename the character name to your other character.<br>
<br>
<br>
Multiple skins for multiple characters:<br>
<br>
- Open the UI.ini file for your character. Find the [Main] section.<br>
- Edit the line that reads UISkin=Default to UISkin=&lt;your skin folder&gt;.<br>
- Save the ini file.<br>
- Do this for however many characters you want different skins for. <br>
